-- Galfar, Larsen Win $764 Million Contract to Develop Oman's Salalah Airport
-- B y   S h a j i   M a t h e w
-- 2010-11-14T05:06:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-14/galfar-larsen-win-764-million-contract-to-develop-oman-s-salalah-airport.html
Galfar Engineering & Contracting
SAOG, an Omani construction company, said a venture with
Larsen & Toubro Ltd. won a contract valued at 294.1 million
rials ($764 million).  The contract is for the development of the Salalah
international airport, Galfar said in a statement on the Muscat
bourse. The completion period is 30 months, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  